<solution>
<p><ul><li>5.49</li></ul></p><p>Because it does not matter which leg is a and which is b we call the missing leg x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{4.31}^{{2}}={6.98}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}+{18.5761}={48.7204}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={48.7204}-{18.5761}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}^{{2}}={30.1443}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{x}^{{2}}}}=\sqrt{{{30.1443}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{5.49}</m>.</p>
</solution>
